Go to the Maidens Fancy in 3rd Gate.  Notice the giant troll named Ratraz.  He is a level 19 warrior.  He ALWAYS drops a warclub, sellable to the merchant in same bld for 5pp 3gold with 70 Charisma, about 1 in 4 times drops words, runes, gems and cash loot from 6 silver to over 1pp.<br>
Strategy:<br>
Pull at least a 17th level pet, or ratraz will kill you quick and totally ignore your pet.  Give pet Burnout and fireshield.  Mana to at least 90%.  Do /pet attack.  As soon as pet attacks, start nuke'n Ratraz for all your worth, usually takes 4 hits with Shock of Flame before he starts running.  It is imperative you make your pet attack first, or ratraz will kill you.  He double attacks for 40, kicks for up to 18 and bashes for up to 11 so far.  This means you get stunned a LOT so stay out of melee.  I started killing him at 17 and never died, but got close a few times until I figured out the strategy.  His spawn rate really blows...about 11 minutes.  Note:  Nothing will aggro onto you while killing him <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  You take 3 faction hits...simple remedy.  Buy red wine from the vendor at 6 silver each (pimp change) and take to the library - the only room in library with a door houses a scribe, who says he don't have time to talk to you.  Give him 4 bottles of wine max each trade window, and you will get exp (minimal) and faction adjustments which directly clear up those taken for killing ratraz.  It takes about 4 wines per kill to keep faction even.  I usually keep my faction to con kindly.<br>
ALSO in same room is Malon Tplth, a 16th level rogue.  This guy is tougher than Ratraz, as I've never been able to get him to aggro onto my pet.  To kill him, buff pet and fireshield YOU, not pet.  Start with a nuke, then run like mad around in circles in the room.  The pathing there is weird, so malon will not be able to follow you, but instead goes around tables instead of coming straight at you.  Just keep running like mad (never tried SOW) and every now and then toss in the nuke.  Yes, he's killed me at 17, but not since.  He has absolutely NO loot, cash or anything, but he fills in the dead time of the slow Ratraz spawn.  You take a faction hit against the EbonMask for killing him, and quite a few pluses for non-DE guilds. <br>
There's also supposed to be a Ironforge prisoner downstairs in a room named Tayla Ironforge that's level 16, but in about 8 hours camping Ratraz, I've never been able to find her...????  I've no idea if she has placeholders or some scenerio to be staged, but she's also supposed to be great exp and loot.  If I ever find her, I'll post an update.  If one could get all 3 (Tayla, Molon and Ratraz) kills going, it'd be a great camp, with minimal down-time.<br>
Good luck to all!<br>
-Anthe<br>
